name: ciso8601
summary: fast iso8601 date time parser for python written in c
documentation_summary: The HTML text describes the ciso8601 library version 2.3.1, released on October 30, 2023, available on PyPI (Python Package Index). It is a fast ISO8601 date time parser for Python, written in C, offering significant performance advantages over other Python libraries. The library supports a wide range of Python versions, from 2.7 up to 3.12, and is OS independent. It is licensed under the MIT License and maintained by closeio and tomst. The library provides functions to convert ISO 8601 or RFC 3339 date time strings into Python datetime objects, with support for a subset of ISO 8601 formats and time zone information. It also includes a benchmark comparing its performance to other date parsing libraries, demonstrating its speed advantage, especially for parsing timestamps with time zone information.
